{
  "stem": "19807.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 79.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and I could spot he was white as a ghost.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, being five days about that ship and they were packed like sardines there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was just one incredible emotion to see them and-- and-- and of course, my mother just wouldn't let go once it started.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father was a little bit more reserved, [LAUGHS] you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But my mother just wouldn't let go, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father saw me, but then my kid brother was hanging onto me [LAUGHTER] by-- for dear life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And after that, they went to it's called Ma'Bara, which was like a place of transit.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from there, we took them into a dwelling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father, at that time of all things, he turned farmer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had the place right near a small-- small like a backyard and on his own he developed that backyard and raised bananas.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It blew our mind.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, that was our father, the husband, this is-- but no, he's in Israel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He's going to be a farmer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He became a farmer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So-- and my mother was a housekeeper, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then I took my brother immediately under me and I made sure that he went to the best schools.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Like I said before, he just did not like to study.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He just wanted to do things with his hands, so we put him into a [INAUDIBLE], a very, very excellent trade school and he became a craftsman.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was-- well, he and his partner which graduated the same school, they've been partners for over 30 years.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There's two of them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "What do they do, they do with their hands.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they build-- if you move into a house in Israel, it's only the walls.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
